get.description: To retrieve a list of recent URLs (recent additions made to URLhaus), you must send a HTTP GET request to URLhaus. Please note that the API will return a list of recent additions made in the past 3 days, but will return maximal 1000 entries.

parameters.name: limit
parameters.description: There is an additional (optional) parameter limit that you can use to limit the amount of results to a custom value (max 1000)

get.description: To retrieve a list of recent payloads (recent payloads seen by URLhaus), you must send a HTTP GET request to URLhaus. Please note that the API will return a list of recent payloads from the past 3 days, but will return maximal 1000 entries.

parameters.name: limit
parameters.description: There is an additional (optional) parameter limit that you can use to limit the amount of results to a custom value (max 1000)

post.description: To retrieve information about an URL, you must send a HTTP POST request to URLhaus.
To retrieve information about a host, you must send a HTTP POST request to URLhaus
To retrieve information about a payload (malware sample) that URLhaus has retrieved, you must send a HTTP POST request to URLhaus
To retrieve information about a tag, you must send a HTTP POST request to URLhaus

URLhaus tries to identify the malware family of a payload (malware sample) served by malware URLs. Unlink tags, the signature is something that the reporter of the malware URL can not influence. To retrieve information about a signature, you must send a HTTP POST request to URLhaus
